messages.content: Actually, I have already seen this  but mine is still not working.
Do I need to build or the worker runs in run dev mode too?
building gives me this error.  [vite:worker-import-meta-url] Invalid value "iife" for option "output.format" - UMD and IIFE output formats are not supported for code-splitting builds.

I remember seeing such error before after upgrading from snarkyjs to o1js but the issue disappeared after removing worker, and replacing it with lazy loading instead. Unfortunately, I never got time to investigate the real root cause.
So, you can give it a try without worker.

Note that o1js uses web workers internally as well. So, if it runs at all, it's in fact running successfully with o1js' internal workers.

Which means workers should be doable 😄
It looks to me that o1js is currently built as ESM and CJS bundles. If you try to build o1js as UMD or IIFE, I suspect you will run to similar error like above.
Finally , Worker is running but in dev mode only.
I had to tweak some things in my project.
@t4top could you build your project earlier using snarky?
Yes, I was able to build using snarkyjs. BTW, I only tag the git repo only after successful build and deployment.
Can you share the tweaks you made?

Check out my Github repo:
In the ZkappClient.ts file  I used the `?url` style for importing the worker.
https://github.com/rudrakpatra/zkchess/blob/main/ui/src/lib/zkapp/ZkappWorkerClient.ts#L3 
The added a `configurePreviewServer` in vite.config.ts 
https://github.com/rudrakpatra/zkchess/blob/main/ui/vite.config.ts#L14 
Current state of the repo, Worker works in dev mode.
Project builds successfully but after building, the worker file has the following error.
